    <h2 id="why-compliance">Why Compliance Beats Dose (Most of the Time)</h2>

    <p>Skin benefits from collagen require <strong>12+ weeks of consistent daily use</strong>. This is non-negotiable — every positive clinical trial used at least 8 weeks of daily supplementation, with peak effects at 12+ weeks. Stop for 1-2 weeks and your skin benefits reverse.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A 2018 survey of 3,200 supplement users found that <strong>68% of people stop taking powder supplements within 30 days</strong>, while <strong>84% continue gummy supplements past 90 days</strong>. The #1 reason cited was "too much hassle" — scooping, measuring, mixing, cleaning the shaker. For collagen specifically, where you need 12+ weeks of consistency, this compliance gap means gummies often produce better real-world results despite lower per-serving doses.</p>
      <cite>Supplement Compliance Survey, 2018</cite>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <span class="tip-box-ico">&#128161;</span>
      <p><strong>The honest test:</strong> Ask yourself — will you ACTUALLY mix powder into coffee or a smoothie every single morning for 3 months? If yes, powder is the best value. If "probably not always," choose gummies. A $25 bottle of gummies you take daily beats a $50 tub of powder that sits unused after week 3.</p>
    </div>

